data -> table -> database -> database server / (s/w)


there are two types of databases -
------------------------------------
    1. SQL   Database   : MySQL, PostgresSQL, Oracle
    2. NoSQL Database   : MongoDB

SQL Databases are Structured Databases
because each record 'should' have fixed no. of values.
- value nhi dili tr by default NULL gheto.

NoSQL databases are Unstructured Databases
because each document may be different size.
        --> NoSQL madhe 'document' mhnte ani SQL madhe 'Record' mhntat.
- jevdhya value dyal tevdhech value ghete no extra/default value.
- table  la 'Collection' mhntat
- record la 'Document'   mhntat
- each document is stored in KEY : VALUE pair.
    yalach js madhe JSON FORMAT mhntat.